### Simple Definition

`preventDefault()` batata hai browser ko:  
**“Jo default action hone wali thi, usko mat karo.”**

### Common Real-World Examples

| Event                          | Default Behavior                          | preventDefault() kya karta hai? |
|-------------------------------|-------------------------------------------|---------------------------------|
| Form Submit                   | Page reload / redirect                    | Form submit hone se rokta hai |
| Link (`<a>`) Click            | Page pe navigate karta hai                | Link follow hone se rokta hai |
| Right Click (Context Menu)    | Context menu kholta hai                   | Right-click menu rokta hai |
| Checkbox / Radio Click        | Automatically check/uncheck               | Check hone se rok sakta hai |
| Drag & Drop                   | Default drag behavior                     | Custom drag-drop control |
| Touch / Scroll events         | Page scroll                               | Custom scroll logic |

### Basic Syntax

```js
element.addEventListener('eventName', function(event) {
  event.preventDefault();     // Default action rok diya
  // ab aap apna custom code likh sakte ho
});
```

### Practical Examples

**1. Form Submit Rokna (Sabse Common)**

```html
<form id="myForm">
  <input type="text" required>
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>
```

```js
const form = document.getElementById('myForm');

form.addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();        // Page reload rok diya

  // Ab aap apna custom validation + AJAX call kar sakte ho
  console.log("Form submitted without reload");
});
```

**2. Link Click Rokna**

```js
const link = document.querySelector('a');

link.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();        // Link follow nahi hoga
  alert("Link clicked but page didn't change");
});
```

**3. Right Click Disable (Context Menu)**

```js
document.addEventListener('contextmenu', function(e) {
  e.preventDefault();
  alert("Right click is disabled on this page");
});
```

### Important Points (Must Remember)

- `preventDefault()` sirf **default browser behavior** rokta hai. Event bubbling ko nahi rokta.
- Agar aap bubbling bhi rokna chahte ho to `event.stopPropagation()` use karo.
- `preventDefault()` ko sirf **cancelable events** pe hi asar hota hai.
  - Check kar sakte ho: `event.cancelable` (true/false)

### When to Use `preventDefault()`?

- Form submit karte waqt (AJAX ke saath)
- Custom dropdowns, modals, tabs
- Drag & Drop functionality
- Keyboard shortcuts (e.g., Ctrl+S)
- Anchor tags jo JavaScript se handle hote hain

### Best Practice

```js
button.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
  if (someCondition) {
    e.preventDefault();     // Sirf tab rokna jab zaruri ho
  }
});
